<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 11:16PM CDT  by NWS Springfield</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Bourbon
County through MIDNIGHT CDT...
At 1115 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Uniontown, or 15 miles southeast of La Harpe, moving northeast at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Fort Scott, Marmaton, Bronson, Uniontown, Redfield, Petersburg, Devon
and Porterville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
